\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid4921470 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Can you tell me your full name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Alexander MacLeod.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 38 Newton Street, Stornoway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 And your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 1903.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 And your year of marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 '35.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 And birthplace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 The place you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Back. Back area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How many years did your family live in that house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh as to that I just - can't tell you, I was born there - I was born 1903, probably - the house would be built in 18 - in the 1890's sometime. And - it's still lived in, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 But you yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh me? I - I'm a - a r
over. I went off - I went off to sea in 1923, I went sailing a - bit, not - not an awful lot. Then I went - over to - the United States. Took - twelve and a half years over there, come back. In 1935. I got married on Thursday, sailed home on Friday. I had
 an Atlantic honeymoon. So - we've been here ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 So you lived there until the end of 1918 anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes. From - lived there 'til 1923.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Can you tell me how many brothers and sisters you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I had five brothers - and two sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Where were you in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I'm - I'm in the middle, exactly in the middle. Four ahead of me, four behind me. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Can you tell me how they went, who were the eldest four for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 The - oldest - was a sister. The next was - 
my brother. The next was another sister, the next - well the whole lot, all of them after that were boys. There were six of us, six boys and two girls. And one died in infancy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 A boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Mm. No, a girl. Well not in infancy exactly - very early in life, maybe fourteen or fifteen months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 So when you said there were nine of you were you including that sister or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 She was one of those first two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How many years between?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh, about three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you happen to know how old your father was when you were born, or any way you could work it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How old he was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you know his year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, I don't know his year of birth. But I could figure out - I could figure it out. He wa
s fifty-nine - fifty-nine when he died, he was born in - he - he died in 1927.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about your mother, was she older or younger than your father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 She was - a couple of year younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What area did your father came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Same area. Same area. And my mother the same area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Your father's occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Fisherman mostly. Crofter fisherman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 He got some of his money from both sources did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Cr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2911776\charrsid16062691 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
fting - a few sheep. Cow or two. But fishing was - fishing was the - the earning - the earning - labour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did that last all the year round, the fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, except when - when the weather was unclement, when it was - stormy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 It wasn't like herring fishing where there's a season?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about your mother, did she have a job before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Well of course - what - we called - going to the fishing. For - girls. They were gutters, herring gutters. When the herring was being cured - then they had to be gutted first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did they work in a team of three girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 That's right. That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 After she started having her family did she ever do any work outside the home again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh no, I think she had more than enough to do. Yes, quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you remember any married women with children going back and doing any gutting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh, on occasions she did. Quite a - quite a few of them when there was - particularly when there was a glut of herring up here and they couldn't get - enough people to handle it. Quite a few of the women from our are
a come up and - did that - a day's work and the walked home. There was no cars or taxicabs or anything. They walked home. And walked back - walked to work. Seven miles in the morning and - seven miles in the evening.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When she did that do you remember who looked after the youngest children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh - well, the oldest looked after the youngest, it was just a case of - progressing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I wonder if you could describe to me your house which you grew up in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well it's - was - one of the first - what 
we call - white houses. At one time it used to be all - a black house, thatched houses. But this was one of the first - outside a government building, Post Office and school houses and so on, that - was built in that area. It's a nice little house, still 
is a nice little house and could be made very nice but - my older sister is getting a wee bit past - looking at it as far as repairs is concerned. But it's still a nice little cottage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Where was the fireplace then in the white house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Fireplace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 It wasn't in the middle any more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, no. No. Fireplace in each end. Each gable end. In fact you could see it if - if you had the - a lot of time to rove around. Aye.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How many actual rooms were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh four rooms yes. Yes. There's an upstairs and downstairs and - two rooms up, two rooms down. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were three of the rooms used for sleeping and one for living, was it like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, three, mostly - the youngsters - slept upstairs. My father and mother slept - in the far end
 room. Maybe with - with one of the babies, sleeping with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you have the box beds in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Box beds? No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Ordinary bedsteads were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh - they weren't - they weren't - what we call iron bedsteads, they were - they were
 wooden bedsteads but they didn't have the canopy on, they were just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did they have those often do you know?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes, they had. They - they had not - not nowadays hardly, but - there were some of them. In fact most houses, even this house, I co
uld show you places in it - was laid out - with small alcoves in it, to - well a recess to take your bed like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you ever have anybody else besides your family living with you, like a granny or auntie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh quite often, quite often my granny - was - the nanny. When there was a youngster - she - she was with us for a while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was that your mother's mother or your father's mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 That was my mother's mother. She - she had three daughters, my - my mother had two sisters. And they all 
had big families, and my granny was kept on the hop, from one house to the other - as - as the family arrive - families arrived - doing the chores.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 They both lived in the Back area too did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you ever have a lodger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Not in my years there. But when the family scattered - I think they had a - a schoolmaster or - a senior - schoolteacher there living.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did your mother ever pay anybody to help in the house with the housework or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Can you tell me how the washing was done at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Usually - is usually in a tub. In a wooden tub, a hogs head, part of an hogshead cut in two, and maybe once a year - blankets and curtains and everything were all carted down to the river. And done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 In the cold water in the river?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, well yes, and they used to build fires by the riverside. And oh the washing day at the river was a big day. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Would several women gather together for that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh usually they made a - a date between them and - had - a few of them go together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Can you tell me if your mother made any of the clothes in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh aye, a lot of them. A lot of them. She - oh - all - all - all the mothers in my day had to. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you use your own wool from the sheep for your own clothing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Yes, sometimes. We weren't - quite - so - so keen on doing that because we were kept busy - at the fishing, we had two boats when I was at sea and - that kept us on the hop. That - that's why I - I - I wanted to po
int out - the - habits and - in different areas - over on the west side they couldn't go out fishing, it was very stormy, the stormy Atlantic - coming in there. Well they had to - were allowed to whatever was available, wool - converted into yarn, yarn in
to cloth, tweed and so on. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 So on the whole was your cloth bought, readymade cloth bought by your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. Yes, they had - they had - a type of - a tweed - what we call in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2911776\charrsid16062691 G}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 aelic clorbuchach - a well made - somewhere on the east coast of 
Scotland, but used quite a lot by the - by the Morayfirth fishermen, and of course we called them buckachs and it was clorbuckoch, that was - tweed as used by the - the Buckie. There there was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Can you spell that word for me please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Pardon? Buckach. That's a - that's - that's our }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2911776\charrsid16062691 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 aelic for buckie. Buckach. Buckach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 And the Clor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Clor. Clo. That's clo like clomore, that's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2911776\charrsid16062691 H}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 arris tweed. Clomore is a type of - type of - of worsted. Clo.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was that quite a heavy bluish colour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. No, not bluish. It was brownish. A - that's - the blue was the serge, what we call the serge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 A lot of men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2911776\charrsid16062691 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 s clothes were made out of the serge were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, pilot serge and - so on. Helyard. And that helyard on - this - called buckach but - heavier than the general run of - cloth nowadays.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did your mother actually sew the clothes or did she give it to a tailor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, she sewed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 She did it all, the men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2911776\charrsid16062691 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 s clothes too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 They couldn't afford - they couldn't afford to sen
d it to the tailor. You went to the tailor for your Sunday suit. But - the rest mostly was - home made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 By hand or with a sewing machine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 By hand - as - in those days very few people had a sewing machine. It's only when my - my older sister - st
arted - going to the fishing - gutting - and the Singer began - ferrying these machines around. All the girls - that were at the fishing bought a machine. Then of course they were - busy at it all with them making blouses and dresses and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about boots, did you go barefoot in the summer or did you wear boots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Barefoot, yes. Barefoot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Where were your boots got, did you have boots for the wintertime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes. We got one pair and they were nursed very very - minutely because - whe
n you were out playing, you were playing football or anything like that - you had to - had to be examined practically every night to see that - these tackits were still - still there for - protecting the leather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Who repaired the boots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh there was a shoemaker or two in - in - in our district.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did your father ever do them as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh yes, we used to. In fact we had a last and - we had the gear for practically - every trade, you had to, when - when you have a - a - a horse and cart and
 gig and harness - sails for boats, masts - yardarms and so on - you've got to be - a handyman. You can't very well have - somebody there, a tradesman's rates. You've got to do it yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did your father ever do any sewing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Sewing? I don't think he did - sewing, but he was a very good cutter. A very good - cutter.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did he cut out things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, in fact - quite a few people in the area came to him - to cut their garments. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did he use a pattern or did he do it out of his head?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh I think he made his own patterns. Yes. He was very handy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did he do a bit of joinery too and make thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 He had to. YES, we had to. Carpentry, sail}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2911776\charrsid16062691 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 making }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2911776\charrsid16062691 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
 saddlery, shoemaking - or at least cobbling, and what have you, aye, you had to be able to do everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 So if anything went wrong with the boats he did all that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh yes. Unless it was very grave, unless it was very serious - maybe then - I have a - a boat builder was - but otherwise, if it was a minor repair - I used to do
 - the same, bit of - same making - putting - extending the sails, and - everyone in the household, you had to. It wasn't a case of I can't do it, well go ahead, it's got to be done, do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When was that sort of work done, the nets repaired and that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Well use - the - the - the nets were usually repaired in the wintertime. When the herring season kind of closed. That was the nets, but then there was - the line fishing, it was line fishing we were at. And that - you had to do that every - after - e
very time you came ashore. Because dogfish and the likes of that - tore the hooks off on the snoods, and that had to be redone again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was that usually done after tea in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes, well sometimes - quite late at night. At certain times 
of the year - the fish behave - differently, around certain seasons. Then a summertime, we could go out fishing - in the evening, in the - early evening and come - come back home in the late evening. But then again - in the wintertime and - and the - earl
y spring - we leave - left at two in the morning. And - shot the lines - and we began pulling them in, pulling them a - a board - just about time daylight broke. Then, back home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How old were you when you started going out with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 The first time I remember going out was barefoot. At eight - eight years of age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were you excited?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh - I felt - I felt like the king with two crowns on him. Going out on a boat with a sail on it. I didn't feel cold feet or anything else. I mean in - in actuality or in nerves. No, I was quite happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did all the brothers go out at one time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Yes. Yes. Except my younger brother of course. My father had died before he had got - up to any age. That the would - be doing fishing and of course my mother had had to part with the boats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you remember if clothes were got for any particular season of the year or any particular festival like Christmas or anything like that?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Our clothes were got when you required them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 There wasn't a special time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When they wore out I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Your father was very very busy with all the work to do with the fishing, but do you remember if he did anything to help with the domestic chores in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Mm, n
o, he wouldn't have time. He wouldn't have time. My sister of - my oldest sister of course, she was - next in command as far as the - the kitchen was concerned. And very good at it too. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you think your father could have baked something if he'd had to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh yes. Oh yes, but - they had - they did when they - going away to the fishing. They didn't go home every night when they were - fishing out of - out of Stornoway here, and - they had - a cook, a male cook on the boat, but if he - if anythin
g was wrong with him he - they had to do their own cooking, they had to do their own meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You were saying he was a good handyman, did he paint and decorate your house when it needed it? Or would your mother do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh no, she - well - they di
dn't paint. They didn't paint it, they couldn't - they couldn't afford to paint it. They - paint - he painted the windows, the woodwork and so on. I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2911776\charrsid16062691 t was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691  usually a lime - or a whiting that was used - for decorating purposes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 And would he do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh no, he - he wouldn't be allowed to, he - he - that was the woman's - department. Oh around the fire and we had our lines here and lines there and - the lord help you if you - if you didn't watch out and leave - leave that tidy for the weekend anyhow.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 They were quite particular about the fireplaces?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes, and for - round the windows and - and everything. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Can you remember anything else that was particularly a woman's job? Who milked the cows for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 They did. The - the - the women. Women.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did the women plant, did they have lazy beds round that part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
No. They didn't have lazy beds, but the women - all helped in the field. With - spades, there was no - hardly - hardly any ploughing done in our area and that. It 
was spade work. And of course a big family had the advantage to - could all pile into it and get it over in a hurry. Yes. Oh some of the - ladies down in our area were better - better with a spade than many men. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did both men and women actually sew the seed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you ever remember your father doing anything for you or the little children in the way of putting you to bed or washing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 He would, he would if - if there was a - well an emergency but - that wasn't left to h
im otherwise. But - we did all our - all - he did all our - hair cutting and all our - shoemaking, 'til - 'til we boys - got up - to an age where - well all right, you have a go now, it's about time you were - learning to cut - your brother's hair and - r
epair your own shoes and so on. You were - you weren't left to - as a hot house flower at all, you were just - just told to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Have you any recollection at what age you were told to do a bit of haircutting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh - when I was old as - when I was - older - older brothers than me and they had priority. I'd be about - twelve or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You went out with your father in the boat, did he go for walks, that kind of thing, or didn't people do that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No they didn't really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 They walked to get to a place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
They walked to get there. Unless they - if they didn't go - for a walk - as an amusement or pastime. They went for a purpose, for walks. And it was all walking you know, was no riding. Uh huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did he ever have a bicycle -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Not he, no. No. Oh bicycle -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 They were luxuries were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. Yes, that was - I think - oh, I - I - I don't suppose there'd be - a dozen in our area altogether in - my time, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you ever remember him telling you any stories about the past or his life or fairy stories or anything of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Not that I know of. We had so many - tragic stories - that - in fact in - in that area a man was - in a period of - twenty, thirty years there was over p over sixty lives lost - at sea in the - o
n the boats. One night - one night in - wait - 1894, 5 or six, I'm not sure, Mr Morrison could put you right, Mr Morris}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2911776\charrsid16062691 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
n in the library. He could put you right on that. Was nineteen from one - nineteen people - drowned out of - from this house up to the e
nd of the street, on the one street. My grandfather and my uncle was one of - well two of them. And there were - one, two, three, four - four fathers and son - in that area and our four brothers, three brothers in one household. So - we had plenty of stor
ies. Bad ones. They were - they were a hard working lot - they got their living - the hard way. And still they enjoyed it. And much }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2911776\charrsid16062691 more so than - the people, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 leeches I say around the corals here, going up to - the Labour Exchange or - the M }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13964276 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691  I, for th
eir livelihood. No. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Could your father read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Read? Oh yes, he could read. Yes, he could read and write.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 And your mother too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 My mother - my mother wasn't much of a reader, she could read }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2911776\charrsid16062691 G}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 aelic. But he - he could - he could write a beautiful letter, he was - he had a lovely hand - writing hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did they speak English too?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh yes. Oh yes. Well you had to. Going away - yearly to the east coast, conducting all their business in the English. When they were fishing from - Buckie and Peterhead and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Down to Yarmouth did they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, sometime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You were telling me about the work at the fishing, did you have any other jobs you had to do such as carrying peat for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes - that was the - that was the
 fuel. March, April. April - everybody went out - and cut their own peats, each household - had a share in a - in - in the common grazing had a peat - a peat share you see. You didn't cut anywhere at all, you cut on your own share. And - that of course en
tailed - waiting - maybe two weeks, three weeks - before they were - dry enough to - lift, and then they were re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2911776\charrsid16062691 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
lifted, you know, and - not stacked up but just - fours and fives like this, for the warm to get through and dry them. Then about - maybe - a mo
nth, six weeks after they were cut, you gave them what we called a second - second lift. And after that of course - start to ferry them to the road. In those days it was horse and cart all the time. No lorries. Horse and cart. Which was a very lengthy pro
cess because - these carts - it's not that the horses wouldn't - wouldn't - pull it but - the carts were small and the roads were bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you share the horse with the other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, we had ours. Aye. In fact we went - we hired out - to many people - taking home their peats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was it men who cut the peats or did young boys help in that too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Men, boys - the family again. The ladies again. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 The whole family was involved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 The - aye. Excepting of course - these that were in 
school. But - on Saturdays - the whole - family piled in and - even a couple of peats now and again was a help. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were children ever in your family kept away from school to do work of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No, unless there was somebody sick in the h
ouse. If there was somebody sick, but - not - you wouldn't - I couldn't say that they were deprived of an education - for the purpose of - of doing any work, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you have any other jobs to do, was there anything else you can think of you had to do in the way of household work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
No, I - just except everyday tasks the men - more or less did their own end and - women their own - side of things which kept things going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well - you got a big - slab of pumice stone, and all the knives and forks were - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2911776\charrsid16062691 sc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11869000\charrsid16062691 our}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2911776\charrsid16062691 ed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
 - thoroughly scoured and polished on - well with a - with a cloth, and that. Then of course cleaned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about cleaning boots, did you do your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, we did our own - when there was none at all, sometimes there wasn't any, unless you going some - somewhere special. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you remember the older children in the family looking after the younger ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes. Yes, I - I had my spell of it. You got your spell of that, as you grew up. I - I - had my share of - attendi
ng the very youngest. While the others were out helping my mother - working and my father maybe - in other parts of the country at the fishing. Aye, you're talking about changes. Yes, there has - been quite a few changes. Some of them I don't like. Some o
f
 the changes. And - the ones that I - that I don't like are the ones that - seem to make us - so callous - towards our fellow creatures. In those days that I'm talking about, if there was anybody sick in the village, the whole community piled in, and see 
that their work was done. And - nobody had - a lot, but whatever there was they shared. And that's a - that's - what we - aye -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 That doesn't happen even in the rural parts now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No it doesn't that's what I'm saying, that - with the modern chan
ges - there are others which - I'd rather do without. YES. Oh there - there were - there were very very good like that on the outlying - districts. They wouldn't see - if there was somebody that was taken ill or - there was a death in the family or anythi
ng of that kind, they wouldn't see the - that household's work - lagging behind, everybody piled in and - brought it up to the mark.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did your mother have friends or was she more with her family, or were there people not connected to her by marriage tha
t she was on good terms with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh yes, plenty of friends. In fact the neighbours were all her friends. And you - you - you never knocked on a door going I there hardly. Just walked in, walked out and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did people often sit in each other's house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. Quite often. That's what we call a caelig. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did that quite frequently happen in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. - Yes, but - there's no caeligs now, that's another of the changes that I don't like because - nowadays you've got to wait for an en
graved invitation to get to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 That's a big loss isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 It is. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When people came what did they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 They used to have a sing-song sometimes, the younger crowd. Then - tell stories. Fairy tales. Then - strong man tales, and so on,
 anything to pass the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did they dance as well, the younger people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Hardly - hardly - round the houses - if there was - if they fancied dancing they'd - pick on a crossroads or - or a bridge somewhere. Dancing at weddings and so on, but - not so much in the household. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Would most people allow young people to meet in their house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 There wasn't a split between the generations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 There was no teenage problem,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 In fact, during the war year
s - during the first world war years - people were glad to see - see young or old then because - some of them with their husbands away, were quite lonesome. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You were telling me about looking after the youngest children, were you left in charge with one or more than one child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 On usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 From what age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh - if he wasn't big enough to walk to the peats - maybe three, four, bit if he was older than that, we had to be out, all of us, yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Would you be left with a child the whole day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh no, not - not - not a whole day. Just between meals. And make very sure that - it was between meals. Make sure that the child got fed and - washed - cleaned if he - that was necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 So it wasn't just the girls who were responsible for younger children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well you see - like in our family, there wasn't a girl - except the ones that were able to do some work and help with the - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 So the boys had to do some of that and other work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Can you remember if the youngest children did anything to help the older ones? Can you think of anything they did to help them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Not that I - can't recall - anything to memory just now. We just - just amused them, we just - I tried to amuse - well whoever was - in my c
harge and - sometimes I was - I can tell you a story about that too. My youngest brother - nearly got dorwoned over my nursing. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How did that happen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well I had a - had a boat, at least a - a - a toy boat. You made your own toys. You didn't - there was no Woolworth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11869000\charrsid16062691 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
s, there was no - you - you made your own boat. And of course I was dead keen to try this boat out to see how it would behave, sailboat and all. And one - this day that I - as left in charge, I went to the pond with the boat a
nd I got the young fellow now, stay there, don't - don't move away. And I let the boat go, took my eye off the young one and the next thing I heard was the splash. There he was, down into the pond. I got - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11869000\charrsid16062691 I got big}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691  when my mother came home. She knew right
 away what had happened. And the boat was burned. That was the - that was the sad part. The boat was put in the fire. I left you in charge of - your brother and you nearly drowned him so - you'll have to do without a boat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 She didn't hit you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh no. No, she was very - and - I - I don't remember my father ever hitting any of us, he didn't have to. All he had to do - that was enough. Yes. That was enough.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were there any other punishments they gave you, like sending you to bed early?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Well sometimes yes, if you was real naughty, you had to go to bed early and sometimes without your supper. And - when you started yawing about three in the morning you began to regret your - your action. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When you were a child from about five years old to nine years old, do you remember what time you were expected to be in bed at night?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
I don't think there was any definite time given. By the time we got through playing we were so exhausted that - we went to bed - in reasonably good time.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11869000\charrsid16062691  I - we weren't - stay up later}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691  at all, we - just exhaust yourself playing football or on the shore or something like that and - when you got hungry - went home and - from there, to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You had to something to eat when you got home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did your mother not need to call you in then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh no, no, no, maybe we - we'd be miles away. She couldn't look at - she couldn'}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11869000\charrsid16062691 t watch the whole - the whole b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 rood, they just had to fend for themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You wouldn't get run over by cars at that time of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
No. There were no cars to run you over. Mind you, we could get into accidents - fall down rocks and - fall into the sea and - so on and so forth, but - that was - part of the drill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you remember ever being put to bed when you were a very little boy? Or did you always just take yourself off to bed when you were tired?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
I - we - when I was being put to bed - I was too young to remember. By the time - I was able to put my own clothes on and put them off I went to bed
 on my own. With - in a group. There was three of us, I think three sleeping in the one bed or two at least, and - just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were you all boys in one room, you'd have had to have been boys and girls together wouldn't you to some extent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well - they were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 They weren't fussy about that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No they weren't fussy and - the girls were so much older than we were that - they had their own - bedroom, bedroom anyhow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You were saying as soon as you could take your own clothes on and off, how di
d you manage about bathing in those days, there was no bathroom in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
No. Oh you - my mother just took us and - got a basin and you got a sponge - and that was it. And of course, when the summer was like this you didn't need a bath, you - we 
were in the sea without - without end swimming away and - if not on the sea we were on the moor, in the rivers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did the girls swim too or just the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. The girls didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When did you have clean clothes to put on, was there a regular day or just when they were needed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 About the weekend, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were there special clothes for Sunday for children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, not while - not for the younger crowd. People who went to church, they dressed up for Sunday and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 But the younger children didn't go to church in Lewis did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
No. They were - they might go to Sunday school. They went to Sunday school, and of course they had to have their best bib and tucker on there, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, but - not as much as I should have. I was a bit of a rebel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Didn't you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh I liked it all right but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you like other things more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 There was too much - repetition. Yes. Oh I - I - I'd far rather be out playing than be in Sunday school. I - I think we all would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you start going to church services at a certain age? Or did you not go?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I couldn't say, I think about - fourteen, fifteen I started - going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you have to wear a suit to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Can you tell me a little bit about the family's meals, where did you all eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well mother just - like a - like the kitchen and a big table. Sometimes a huge - basket piled with fish, another one piled with potatoes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you help yourselves from those dishes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. Quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How old were you before you used a knife and fork,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh - as to that I couldn't tell you. Probably eight or nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Up 'til then did you use a spoon or your fingers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh a spoon or our fingers, anything that could - would hold food, all I was concerned with was getting into it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What sort of cooker or fire did your mother have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 A peat fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did she have any kind of oven at all, or stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Just a peat fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Mm hm, a peat fire. Open fire. And the cooking was done on - cast iron pots mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 So food wasn't roasted, it was only boiled or grilled?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Very seldom roasted, they could roast in these - cast iron pots too you know. But it was mostly boiled.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you have porridge for breakfast in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Quite often, yes. Sometimes broes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Broes is another form of porridge. Oatmeal - and hot water poured over the hot - the oatmeal, without being cooked, you know what I mean, and maybe a pat of butter mixed in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 And what about the midday meal, did you have a hot meal at midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Yes. We were very near the - we were very near the school, we were - lucky to - potatoes and herring, potatoes and fish, pota - potatoes and - salt meat -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was that your own meat or did you ever buy meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh we bought meat. We bought meat. And - the custom in those days was - in the autumn the - went to the market and got a cow, killed it between - maybe two or three or four crofters and divided it and 
salted it in, sorted it out. Now, salt fish, salt herring, salt - meat. But - we were fortunate in this respect that - there was always somebody coming up, up the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11869000\charrsid16062691 
 town here, with the fish to se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 ll you see. And quite often there was - fresh meat, as well. Oh
 - aye, we were fairly well off for - for meat, maybe we didn't have - as many delicacies as - not maybe but positively we didn't, the jellies and so on, but - good strong healthy fare, no - no nonsense.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Would you say you had some meat every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about the meals after dinner, did you have tea and then supper or just one or the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 We used to have - tea and what we call supper, our supper at eight, nine o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What did you have for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh - scones, fresh butter maybe - a bowl of - buttermilk or milk or something. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 And supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Supper, potatoes and herring maybe. Maybe - porridge and milk. And - whatever was available, there was no - not much choosing. You just took - what there 
was, you - if you were hungry, you were out in the fresh air all the time. And no, there was no turning up your nose at anything, not - not with my appetite anyhow. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 If you had refused something what would have happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well, there was no alternative. Wouldn't be there for you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about tinned food, did you ever have any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
That didn't exist in those days. Well there was that type of tinned meat. Which - we wouldn't take, we wouldn't eat. We weren't great on it. Bully beef aye. Di
dn't want it. We had - fortunately in our house - what we considered better fare, alternate - salt meat, the fresh meat and - fresh fish. Salt herring, fresh herring. That - now there was a period, in the springtime, the early spring - when things were pr
etty scarce. You couldn't - there was no herring fishing going on. And quite often there were - was - stormy weather. They couldn't go out with the - with the open boats. So then you - relied on the salt store. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about jam, did your mother make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No, we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You would go without jam then would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
No, we - we had jam occasionally - but - didn't care for marmalade, that's the funny thing. People - they like marmalade nowadays but - we'd rather have - the other fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Rhubarb jam is very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about making pickles or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you do any brewing at home, beer or wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Brewing, no. Well some - some crofters did but very few. Very few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did your mother make any home made medicines or remedies for when you weren't well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Yes, there was a brew - made of herbs - that - they used for - blood purification like for boils and - and - stuff like that. What they call - the herb - the weed, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 It wasn't dulce was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
No, no. No, not dulse. Oh dulse was - a bit of a tonic if you're the other way - you could - make pudding out of - out of - a form of seaweed called carracan in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11869000\charrsid16062691 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 aelic, that's where the word carceen comes from.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How do you spell that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Carracans, carracan. Carracan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you ever have puddings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Well that's the only type of pudding. Aye. Of course - no, and - and I'm - I'm wrong. Used to - make a - my mother used to make - a rice pudding, and - in those days - tapioca was
 very popular. That was about the first of the - the - best known - brands of puddings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you ever get any meat from hunting or poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh - yes, I used to get - rabbits - occasionally - a snipe or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was that legal or was that poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh it was legal, well - rabbit rabbit - catching is quite legal here. Yes. All the time. It was not so much - poaching as being darned lucky if you could get one, if you could catch up with one, and nobody going to question you if you went home w
ith a brace of rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about salmon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Salmon. Yes, that was poaching. That didn't keep us from doing it just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were people prosecuted if they were caught by the keepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11869000\charrsid16062691 es}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 ? }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11869000\charrsid16062691 Very seldom}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 . They didn't bother an awful lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 At a mealtime were you allowed to talk and chatter among yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11869000\charrsid16062691 es}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
? providing you kept quiet - while grace was being said, before meal and after the meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Who said the grace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 My father usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate? You say you didn't leave your food?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh - well, if you left your food there was always a query as to whether you were ill or not. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes. Yes. And quite often get it too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 There was never a shortage of food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were you expected to sit in a particular way and hold your knife and fork or spoon in a certain way, were they particular about that?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, not - all they were particular about 
was - that you took enough food, to keep you in good order. That was the main thing. And in our house anyhow, I don't know what they did in other homes, but - my own experience was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When could you leave the table? Was that after the grace at the end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 After the grace, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 So you all waited and got down from the table together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you all have the same seat, every time go to the same place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, not particularly, all depended - how you came in. Quite often some of
 the young - younger ones weren't - at the mealtime, they probably came in before the meal was finished and - and you never know - whenever you - what business - would keep a member of the family away from - from a meal, and - come in there any time and s
it down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 If you came in late you were only supposed to have been kept by business, you couldn't be playing outside and come in late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh, oh, yes, as youngsters, they were - we weren't - no, they weren't fussy. All they were concerned with was tha
t you did come home - and had a good meal. You could play to your heart's content.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 So it didn't matter if you came in after grace was said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 But while you were there you were supposed to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 So you were quite flexible, easy going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What did your parents think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 They didn't think much of it. They were - definitely against it. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in the conversation or make remarks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Not much, you were more or less - to be seen and not heard, when - grown ups were - very much respect your elders. Mm. If your opinion was asked, which was very rare, then you could voice your -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 But you didn't interrupt conversations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Can you remember if you were brought up to hit back and defend yourself if hit by other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh indeed, yes. You couldn't do anything else in our house. Oh was like - Madison Square Gardens at times, you just - took what was coming
 to you or else got away from it. And if you got into trouble in school - if you didn't beat the fellow that was - up against you, well - you'll know better next time, keep away from him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh very respectable. Very respectful. Yes. They expected - us to give them their - place, and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Would you say your mother was an affectionate person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. Both were. I told you my father and never - I don't - think I saw him - hit any of us 
in his life, and there was nine altogether. All he had to do was - mm, just cough. You were - my mother, oh occasionally would have to give us a - a clip on the ear, but not - not - not very hurtful. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 If you had any worries could you talk to your mother about them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh I - I don't remember having any. I don't remember having any worries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 But she was easy to talk to was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh easy to talk to, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 And your father too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What sort of things did your parents bring you up to consider important in life, in your general conduct?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
One thing. Main thing, honesty. Don't - touch anything - that doesn't belong to you. Don't tell lies. Don't swear. But honour life, don't steal anything. No, I - you were allow - you - yo
u - you were excused if you - stole a turnip or a cabbage or a - a stack of - rhubarb or something like that - out of a garden. But I mean - to help yourself to somebody else's property - oh no, that was frowned on very very much, very much, in fact - if 
y
ou came into our house for something - that wasn't yours and - it was known to - be - really out with the family you were questioned, and asked where you got it. And how you got it. And if you couldn't give a satisfactory answers, you would have to go bac
k with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you ever remember that happening to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. Because it was so much discouraged in our house, that we never - never did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about this sort of thing and how to behave from both 
parents, or did one play a more important part than the other do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh I think - about - equal, from each one. Another thing - ano - another thing that I must stress - that my father particularly was - against. Don't m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11869000\charrsid16062691 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 ck an old person. Oh - he was really poison on that, he wouldn't - if he ever heard that any of us - played any tricks on an old person - then you might get a clip on the ear. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was that sometimes done by the boys, playing tricks on old people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well, yes, thoughtle
ssly at times. Not - injurious - tricks, but - things that inconvenienced them, and disturbed their - their peace. Oh he - he frowned on it very strongly, he - just wouldn't have it. His contention was that - if you lived long enough you'd be old yourself
. And to remember and respect - older people like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Good advice wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 It was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I never knew I had a birthday 'til I arrived in New York. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You mean you hadn't heard of birthdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. It wasn't - wasn't even thought of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Can you remember anything you did on Christmas Day which made it different from an ordinary day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 We didn't - we - we didn't bother with Christmas, it was New Year with u
s mostly. The only thing that - well at least - we stayed out at night and - had what we called - what we thought was a ploy of some description, maybe - ditch a cart or two or - throw a - bottle of paraffin where it shouldn't belong and so - the owner wo
uld - get in a tizzy in the morning to look for it, and then we went to - the farm, there was a farm in our area, and the farmer used to give us a barrel of turnips. And dump them and - threw them along - the meadow, for us to scramble - and get one or -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 That was all done at New Year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. New Year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Would the teenagers have a dance or anything then or the older young people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 The only dances that were kept - apart from weddings, there was always a bit of a dance at a wedding, was occasio
nally they'd go down - to the crossroads or to the village and - and have a - bit of a - a hop there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you have any musical instruments in the home, in your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You said yours was a divided home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well - how - who have we - who have we there to - to start before the - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Yes, well - musically our - our family was a divided family. There were six boys. Six sons. Three of them were first class pipers. And three weren
't. Simply because - one - one of the - one three - had a liking for the pipes, to the extent of learning to play the chanter and - learned to play musically. Whereas the rest of us liked - to hear it but - not - enough to practice it. Now - an accordion,
 a different story, I could - spend all night with one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You could play one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh not - not - not - not very good, not like they do now but - there were - music wasn't so easily - taught. We had no recorders, nothing. If you couldn't carra a tune i
n your head - that was you bunkered, you just couldn't do anything about it. But I liked the melodeon. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did your father play anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 He played the melodeon, he was a very good - very good player. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 And your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh no, oh 
no - music was frowned on as far as girls were concerned. Yes. They didn't - no, well very very - rare - girls would play the accordion, very very rare
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 And they didn't play the pipes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 But they sang did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes. Yes. And p
articularly when they were going off - to the fishing. Oh used to be a great concert on the boat here, just before it sailed. Different crews - singing away and - really good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What songs would they sing then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh Gaelic songs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Old songs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Aye. Old songs. Old Gaelic songs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Not religious songs, psalms and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you, your family and relations ever have a sing-song together?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, no we didn't. We didn't. We used to have - a Psalmody class in the church
, for learning psalms, but - I wasn't a great churchgoer, or a - I wasn't inclined that way, I wasn't inclined towards - learning the psalms or music or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 But you liked to listen to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you have books in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 N
o - not very many - but we always had access to the school library. And - the nurse - the nurse in our area was - a great reader, and she used to give me quite a - a lot of books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about newspapers and magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Newspapers - yes, we got - t
he Solway Gazette once a week. That of course - didn't come to the fore 'til about - well - 1913 I believe, I - I'm not sure when - when it - began to be published here. We used to get the Highland News. And - of course - a daily but - the - the daily was
 only weekly. In fact we only had the mail boat - calling three times a week. So that was what - few and far between.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you remember your mother or father reading, sitting reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes, I remember my father reading quite often. But my mother wasn't a great reader. She could read }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6493096\charrsid16062691 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 aelic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did she have books in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6493096\charrsid16062691 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 aelic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh the Bible. The Bible was a - the main reader. There wasn't very many }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6493096\charrsid16062691 G}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 aelic books publications at that time. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did they ever read aloud, or did your father ever read loud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Just to himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you remember a funeral in the family before the end of the first world war, could you describe how the funerals were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well the only funeral in the family - that we had - was my young sis
ter, she was - fourteen months when she died. And of course - an - an infant, a baby - funeral's different from a grown up one. It's only - very few people come to it and - just close relations. Whereas - the town - and the Back area even today, if some -
 
there's a - a burial, the whole community joins. And they - they bear - they carry the bier - for quite a distance, walk it, and then it's put in the hearse and - take it - to the graveyard, that's - nowadays, and - they - walked all the way in those days
. There was no other means of - of transport except maybe a horse and cart.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did children go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No women. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about when the remains were laid out, did people come and visit in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes, they - they had what they called a wake, maybe two, three nights. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Sitting all the time with the body you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes, and - having a - a religious service. Prayers and - singing psalms and - so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 But children had no part in any of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How old would a boy or a girl be before they would attend a funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Well - if it was - a parent like - and family that were unfortunate enough to - to lose their father or their mother, maybe a boy of fourteen would be at the - at the end of - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about in the community though, if it was a neighbour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh well - be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 A teenager wouldn't go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, not very often. Climbing - eighteen, nineteen, twenty, maybe, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were the blinds drawn?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were mirrors turned to the wall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were mirrors turned round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, no. No. No. There were - there were - at one time - during a - a thunderstorm. Some people maintain that there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid871149\charrsid16062691 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 s - an attraction to lightning in mirrors. But - not - not - not in our area anyway that I can remember that - the mirrors were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When your young sister died did you change your clothing at all, did you have to wear mourning clothes for a period after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well we - we didn't, we were too young. We were too young, the - but my parents and - the older members would - dark clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 For how long would they wear dark clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well I don't know - for a youngster like that, but - oh a period of - years I would think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Over a period of years for an adult you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Were you taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relations when you were a child? Would there be an occasion when the family would go out visiting together as a family, did they go out for tea or out visiting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Not very often. No, not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were you ever taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
No. No. The - we used to have - and this is the time of the year for it - we used to have what they called a market day. Where - all the - cattle - that were for sale - in the island co
ngregated right out where the - County Hospital is just now. And - everybody came to town that day, young, old, middle aged and so on. Well not the very old. But - all the youngsters anyhow came to town. That's the only shopping I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were you given some money to spend on that day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh yes. Used to run messages for the whole year - on a promise that - well you'd get this for market and - that for market and so on. And you did - you - they usually fulfilled their promise. They didn't have an awfu
l lot to give you but - an aged person that couldn't - hop around, if you went - to the shop for paraffin or bread or something, well they saw that - around market day you got a little something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No. First time I went away - was - to London sailing - I didn't come back for thirteen years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 That was in 1923 was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. Uh huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How did you spend Saturday when you were a boy, you didn't go to school did you on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. Oh - down the 
shores, sailing boats - and - oh sometimes, certain seasons of the year, we had a football. Other times was - this cat and bat, I don't know - whether you ever played it. Well it's a game - game we called cat and bat. We made a - a wooden cat with - sharp
 ends on it and you had a stick and you hit it and - up, bang oh. It was the - that was the cat, and this was the bat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What exactly is a cat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 The cat was the thing that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 A piece of wood was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 A - a square piece of wood like that wit
h the ends of it - beveled so that when you hit the end - it would spin off the ground. And you had to be quick enough - to hit it with the bat and - put it as far away from you as possible. And then - there were - like baseball, something - of the same o
rder, something like cricket. Except - with cricket it's not running back and forth, you had bases. Cat and bat. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 On a Sunday were you allowed to play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, no, no, you - well you weren't allowed. You weren't allowed to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What were you supposed to do on Sundays besides going to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Sigh and grunt and groan and - kick your heels. Unfortunately there was no provision made - for the young at all, unless you went to church. Some of - some of them went to church, started to go to church very young. Some families did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did services last quite a long time in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. Well - they still last too long with me, because - well the service - lasted at least two hours - then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 There was a long sermon was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, quite a long sermon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about work, what sort of work was allowed on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Nothing. Eseen - just essential work. You weren't supposed to brush your shoes, you weren't supposed to - polish your shoes, you weren't supposed to shave, you weren't - you could wash, but - you weren't supposed to do anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about washing the dishes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes, oh yes, you could wash the dishes. Some people would, other people - drew the line very - very strictly and - what could be
 done and what couldn't be done. Or what should be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was a hot meal cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did your parents feel strongly about these regulations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh I - I can't say - that they did, they weren't as - rigid in their outlook as - some of them. No. they weren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 If children were seen playing on the Sunday, if they were flagrantly playing, would neighbours complain about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 They would and they would - they would caution them about all the - misfortunes that was going - t
o come falling down on their head for - breaking the Sabbath day and so on and so forth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
In those days did adults, other women for example, take responsibility onto themselves for looking after other children in the neighbourhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well yes, if -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Tell a child off if it was doing something naughty without reporting to the mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh yes, ah well, they - they weren't - they weren't bad for reporting it, they - they'd caution you and - leave it at that, they were very good. Very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were there any Sunday school outings, treats and things of that sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Any social activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. None. No. Not in connection with the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Which was this one you belonged to, which Scottish church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well, it's - just the - the Free Church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Not the United Free?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was there a temperance club run by the Free Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You didn't need it - in our area there was no - no - no pub, no booze being sold. Of course there was the usual warning - when - peop
le came up to town here - you could get - you could get drink there but - there was a kind of a temperance movement - on at the time, the - in fact the - there were - this place was - dry for - a number of years. When was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Wasn't it 'til some time in the 1920's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Yes, and - I don't know when it came into operation but it - it was in operation even - the time that I left here because - I remember - and the night we were leaving there was a four and a half here and there, which meant - four and a
 half gallons of beer, you could buy - you could buy it wholesale you see. But not retail So - I don't know when they repealed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were you taught to say prayers at night when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were there family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. Qui
te often - there was family prayers in the morning and at night. And that was one thing that you were - told - to do, to be in at night for the books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was that on a weekday night?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, every night. Every night. Yes, you had to be in for the books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Could you tell me the procedure on this, just reading from the Bible was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Reading from the Bible, there was - a reading and there was a prayer and - those who could sing sang.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was this conducted by your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did your father take an interest in politics when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Not intensely. Well not - I - I paid so little attention to it - that I wouldn't know. I know that - he was - a kind of an agent for some - candidate here. 19 - 1920 I would think. I'm not s
ure. 1919. Well that probably would be. That probably would be it. But I didn't take much - much notice. He - he was - agent for - Michael - Sir Michael Coates I think was his name. They have - they have a shipping - a shipping line down London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Is that Liberal or Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
I don't know either. No. I don't know. That probably would be Liberal. No. No, I don't think it would be Liberal, 'cos I think - the fellow that lost the election that - year was - Doctor Donald Murray. And I think he would be Liberal, I'm not sure.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you remember discussion of politics in the house or in other peoples houses with your father taking part or your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Not a family discussion. Be far more likely to be a discussion of somebody - came in that was on the opposite camp. And there}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid871149\charrsid16062691 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 d be - ah, but it wasn't - wouldn't be so much of a discussion - as an argument. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about your mother, do you remember if she had any views on politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No, she didn't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you know at that tim
e if any men felt that they put their jobs at risk or perhaps risked losing their houses if they voted differently from an employer or landlord? Did that apply?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, I don't think so, because - we didn't have an employer. And - I don't think - the lan
dlord was - politically interested, not to the extent of - running for Parliament here any how.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you know if your father was ever actually a member of the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. Not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 The only activity you remember was with this particular person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did your mother have any interests outside the home and the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
As to that I couldn't say - I - I think - her main interest was - her while there. She might go visiting - a relative now and again but she was very much taken up with the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Her two sisters that you mentioned, did she see them frequently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Her sisters, yes, they're - they're -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How near did they live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well - about half a mile away maybe. They were living - very close together - the other two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Close to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. They were - maybe a mile away from our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Would you say that she ever went out to enjoy herself, have any social activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No, not that I - not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When they had the caelihs, and sat round telling stories, did the women take part in that too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Not the married women - when you got married - you were - that was your politics and your caelighs and your concerts and your picnics - all rolled into one. Whatever - a
ll that, whatever was - done on that - of that it was - the younger ones, the teenagers and - twenty, twenty year olds and so on. But you - you would never find - a married woman going down - to the crossroads to dance. Oh no. Oh no sir. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 There was no pub in your area was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Would women go to a pub in Stornoway if they came in on market day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Not at - in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Not even with their husbands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. - There was one or two individuals who did, and they were known far and wide. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When did your father get home from work in the evenings, there was a very varied pattern?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes. Yes. In fact - when our job - you didn't know when - you would - would be home. It was all sailboats, and it - a lot depended on 
the strength of the wind, and the direction from which it blew, from the fishing ground, maybe you took two hours, three hours - beating to wind}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid871149\charrsid16062691 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 wards, maybe another day - to windward - the wind would be in a favourable direction and you could do that journey in an hour or half an hour. So - there was no set - timetable as far as - the bread}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid871149\charrsid16062691 -win}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 der was concerned. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you think it was a worry to your mother not knowing when your father would be home and how the wind was and the sea and everything?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Yes, it was a worry to them when the winds were high, naturally, but they were brought up to it, and it was - just like - everything else, it grows on you. You get used to it. Naturally when the winds were strong and - there was a danger, they would be
 worried. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You were saying there were no pubs, I don't suppose there was any kind of club your father belonged to? Any sport he took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. Again - again when a man got married - that was his social activities - finished, except of c
ourse - when - he came up town he had a dram or two, whereas if his wife came with him she didn't have a dram. She might have one in the house on the quiet but very very seldom or - very few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 The men didn't play football
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about betting, did your father bet at all,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 There was no betting. No betting shops around or - no means of betting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were there any savings clubs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Savings clubs - nothing outside the banks that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You've told me quite a bit about the way
 you used to play, were there any children round about where you lived that your parents didn't like you to play with, or could you play with all the neighbouring children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I - we could play with any of them. We chose - if there was any - outcasts it
's - the ones that we casted out, not - not our parents. If we didn't get along with them - we didn't play with them, that's all. But not - nobody that I know of - that I was told not to play with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played, get your clothes dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Well, well, we had to, there was no - no paved streets, no pave, nothing here, and you - when you had a football you played it on agricultural ground and - you got - mire up to your - waist. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 There weren't any youth organis
ations, none of these sort of things? Did you ever see anything before the end of the first world war in the way of a cinema or a play, a theatre, a lantern show?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Wait. Yes, I saw a magic - what we called a magic lantern - in the school. Now - I - I 
never saw a - was never inside a cinema - 'til after the war. The first world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you go fishing, well that was the family livelihood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Before you could go out with your father, when you were very small, did you try to fish with a line?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes, rock - rock fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 For little t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4863367\charrsid16062691 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 ddlers and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Yes. Oh yes. In fact - you grew up with the tiddlers. Aye, you were - on the rocks all the time, with the - even a bent pin and - wire and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you have any collections of anything, collect anything like wild flowers or seashells or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
No - no, the only collections that we had - was marbles. Clay marbles in those days, that was - we had a season of that too, that was a game. You played - yo
u played - there was a - a ring, and - marbles in it and - whoever could hit - the most - won the most. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When you were a child and a teenager did you have a special friend or did you just go round with a group of children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 As a teenager, I 
had one or two - particular pals, but I went around with a group, but of course there's always - you always have a - yes, a choice of pal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did boys and girls go round together or did the girls have their own games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well the - the - the girls had
 their own games, and if you were courting a girl - you weren't supposed to be seen with her in daylight at all. No, no. Oh no. At least - not - not on purpose. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Why was that do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I don't know. Can't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What age did boys start courting then, and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh I suppose that's - that's the usual question - some at certain ages, some at other ages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I wondered if it was any later then than it is now, some people think in England that boys and girls pair off earlier than th
ey did perhaps years ago?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Yes, well - yes, that - and - but that arises - also - the fact that they mingle earlier. We - weren't supposed to - mingle with girls for long you know. In fact, not at all supposed to be in theory but we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When your youngest brothers were born and your mother was in bed who helped her in the house then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Well - granny usually did, she - she was - she was the - perennial nanny, she was - and - our house and - my aunties' houses, as the family - and there were - they all had big families, they - there was - eight, none, or ten in then - each family. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
You were saying your parents had friends, would you say that they had the same friends or separate sets of friends? Or were they friendly with all the same people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh as far as I know they were friendly with anybody. Just like communal spir - except of course - close relations, naturally.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You were saying you had your particular pals that you chose, like children always do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were your mother and father the same, did they have one or two or three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh I suppose they had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You don't remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you think of some people belonging to one social class and some to another in the years before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
The only difference - was that - the farmers boy - farmer's son, and daughter, the gamekeeper's - son and daughter, the policeman - the schoolmaster - could be a little better dressed - than we were. But as far as - a social distinction was concerned we 
didn't make any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
What about between the adults themselves, I know you would have been quite a young boy then, but can you remember noticing that there was any distinction between the adults, those adults you mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, they - they seemed to 
- they seemed to associate and - get - integrated into the community just - I - I can't - I can't - remember of any distinction, the only thing was - that financially they were a little better off. They could afford - in the school playground I could - te
ll you - that's - so and so's son, that's so and so's daughter, from - her or his attire. You can't do that nowadays they're all the same, they - one is as well dressed as the other and thank goodness for it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You were talking about those people th
en, would you put everybody else into one group with a similar standard of living, these crofters and fishermen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, more or less - maybe a shopkeeper or two - again finance came into to. If they were a little bit better off financially but - as far
 as - social conditions were concerned - no distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were you brought up to salute or touch your cap or raise your hat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh - oh no. No. No there was - there was none of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Not even the minister?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Jack - Jack - no, Jack's as good as his ma - well - we got out of the minister's way so we wouldn't have to salute him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Would he expect it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I don't think he would expect - to be saluted, he - probably would - expect us to behave ourselves, be - be good boys in presence but - 
no, there was - no - there was no distinction like that made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 And not the schoolmaster either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, he was - just a - better off financially that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 So your parents didn't bring you up to feel that you owed more respect to those people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 They were very democratic in their attitude were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Very democratic. The only thing that they would tell us was that - if we stayed in school and got ourselves an education we might - be in the same position financially as - as these people were - in those days, which I ignored.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were they quite keen that you should have a good education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes, oh indeed, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Is it true, I've been told that in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6247944\charrsid16062691 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 aelic language there's no word for sir or for madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I don't think there is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 So the whole business we have in English, like certain people are called sir, this doesn't apply?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. Uh huh. No. In fact now - in fact I have a - a good gaelic dictionary upstairs. I don't think there is. You'd be - you'd 
be addressed - well a lady or well a woman - well - man, or - well equal or well up here, no - no, no looking up. The only person you were supposed to look up to was the one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You have two personal pronouns don't you, two forms of the word you, there's a respectful form, isn't that so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh - oh there's two or three of them. Yes. Like there and thou and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I wondered if you had to use a different form for elderly people or older people than yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well, some people do. Some people do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were you brought up to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
No. No. Just the one. And - I'm seventy-six now - they are - and to an elderly to an eld - an elderly person I would say - for yourself. But - many people would say - where the distinction is or why I don't know. But
 - different district, different customs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 So in the Back area you didn't use any different forms of address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 It was by your behaviour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was there any, you were Free Church in your area, were most of the people Free Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. Yes, in fact all - all of them down in the Back area are - Free Church. There's no other - denomination there. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Would you say within the group you belonged to that there was a variation in the standard of living or was everybody the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Well again - in - individuality creeps in here. A fellow that was diligent and - made efforts - to prosecute the fishing - that's giving him an average degree of luck, some people were very unfortunate although they would try their 
utmost, things didn't go with them sometimes. Whereas others were very lucky. That applied with the net fishing and with the herring fishing. But it quite often happens that if there's a go ahead - he's better off. That's only natural.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you remember
 any families being thought of as rough families, not as good as other families? And some others as being more respectable among the working people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Now that's - that's very hard to say, I don't think we had - any down in our area that I wouldn't - that I wouldn't - associate with.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 And you think your mother and father were the same?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
I think so, yes. It's so easy - to sit in this corner chair and find yourself better than the other one, but - is it an actuality, is it a fact? Are you - are 
you better or - just equal, I'd like to think that I'm equal with the - with the best, and equal with the worst too, that - there is something in the best of us - that can go just as low as - the worst of us. In other words there - for - but for the grace
 of God go I. Should be thankful that you are - characteristically built in such a way that you can keep your - your passions in check, because it's in every one of us - have deep urges, sometimes that are not so - so - so proper. So -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6247944\charrsid16062691  I'm thankful to my maker, that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
so far I - I haven't been allowed, I haven't been - as I said, I haven't been allowed to - do anything - dishonourable, so - and I don't know of anybody in that area that I would classify as - undesirable. There might be an odd one that I can't -
 bring to mind at the moment, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 It certainly wasn't something you were brought up to think about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
No. No it wasn't. It wasn't. And I - I - I have learned my islander. You know, I - I have a great respect for - people who are - brought up - o
n the edge of poverty and who can rise to such heights. We had some very clever people - leaving this island. Very clever. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 We were talking about the term sir and madam, was the term when you were a child, a gentleman or a lady used of somebody,
 would they say, oh she's a real lady or he's a real gentleman, do you ever remember that sort of way of speaking about people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, as to their character. Y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6247944\charrsid16062691 es}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 . Y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6247944\charrsid16062691 es}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 , but - not - not to their social - position. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was there a distinction between trained craftsmen and labourers at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh - yes. Yes, the - quite a bit. And that's only natural because a person who - serves - an apprenticeship at his craft, he's - I would say he's worthy of his hire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were there several in your area around where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, there were stonemasons, turners - but not - not such an awful lot, not very many because - in the earlier days they went to the milit
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6247944\charrsid16062691 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 a, and others went to our - Royal Naval Reserve, and quite often - they followed from t
he Royal No - Javal Reserve, followed on as merchant seamen and so on. Which - precluded them serving an apprenticeship more or less. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was there a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. Yes. Yes, and I was stealing his - I was ste
aling his gooseberries while he was - tending the - the sheep at the other end of the garden.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did he catch you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, no. No. I made sure of that. But we - we weren't - we didn't - give him much reason to chase us. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How did he treat the people at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Not bad. Not bad, he just became a member of the community. Yes. If he didn't he'd feel - he'd feel it. He'd feel it. Yes, he'd feel it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did your mother ever say, I'll call a policeman if you were doing something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 She didn't use that threat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. I'll tell your father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You were saying that the landlord didn't stand for Parliament, who actually was the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Sire}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10640462\charrsid16062691  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
James Mathieson in those years. And Lord Leverhulme later on. And - the landlord 
at the present time is - the Stornoway Trust. It's gifted, land gifted to them by Lord Leverhulme. So that none of them was that I know of, or anybody in - anybody connected with them, ran for Parliament. Ran for Parliament or - or held any office of that
 nature.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you ever see your landlord, or did he send a factor or a steward or somebody round for the rent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, I didn't see him. And - you pay your rent - or whatever - it is you pay for a croft, and - in the municipal buildings here, in the o
ffice. They don't - they don't send a collector around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was that the same when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What did your father think of the landlord, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh I don't think that I ever heard him - express an opinion about - I don't t
hink so. I know what he thought of Lord Leverhulme. When he came here and - started up - works. He was very happy that - with a family of six sons - they could get a job without leaving the island. But that didn't last very long because - the works closed
 down. Old - Lord Leverhulme had a - bit of a market setback, which resulted in - the works closing down.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When you were a child do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet? Were you conscious of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I don't thin
k I had sense enough to - be aware of it. I just took what was going. Took what was going and - when I got to an age where I could help - I wasn't even asked if I was willing to help, I was told to do it, and - and I did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was your father ever out of work, or ill so that he couldn't earn any money fishing
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was he ill? Not that I know, no, no, not that I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 He always had money coming in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 He was always - out for the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you remember any people in the Back area being fairly d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4010374\charrsid16062691 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 stitute}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4010374\charrsid16062691 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Yes I do. Though illness. One of our very - close neighbours. And that's just a - a - one of the differences - that have - arisen - in modern times. When that man's case was reported to the - poor law officer so that he could get so
me assistance, it nearly broke his heart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
The - the thought of him being - on public assistance was just - a disgrace. And nowadays - they just wondering if there's a - a second angle that they can use to get more. Yes, he was, hon
estly I saw him cry like a baby. The mere fact that - that his - condition - warranted having to be reported to the poor law. Mmm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Do you ever remember on Lewis a system that they have some places in England called rough music, if anybody offended 
against the community people would get together and bang tin cans and things outside their doors several nights in succession, to drive them out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. Not in our day, not to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Before you went to school were you given lessons by anybody or taught anything in the way of school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. They didn't have time. They were - too busy - earning a - getting enough for me to eat and - those that were coming after me. Yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh about - five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You said it was quite near your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, I would - I would say - four or five hundred yards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh just a - an ordinary - grammar school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Mixed, boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You came home for your midday dinner. What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
I was very very keen. Up - to - the time that I started getting - the works from - a schoolmaster we had, and that - that turned me against the school. But I - in the first - seven years I 
was at school, I don't believe I had - two days absent. No, I was very keen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What was it about this particular schoolmaster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh he was rough, he was - he - he used to beat us. He used to beat us about - instead of trying to - teach you, he'd try
 to - bulldoze it into you which can't be done. No, can't be done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was he the same with the girls, did he beat them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 He were rough, he was rough with - with everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about the other teachers? How did you feel about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Some o
f the - some of the - some of the - lady teachers were - very good, very nice. And we had one - male teacher, the senior - the senior teacher there next to the schoolmaster and - he was hard, he was hard on us, punishing us, but a very very good teacher. 
I
 mean he didn't - if he - figured you weren't grasping it - he just didn't bulldoze you, he tried to - lead you by example. But if you did anything wrong, and if you weren't making an effort, you'd get it. Yes. And there was no such a thing in those days 
as - don't use the strap. It was used, plenty. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 For what sort of things? What sort of occasions would they use it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well - if - if you wasn't paying attention, if you - if you didn't make an effort to work out your - arithmetic or you made a 
botch of your - your essay or anything - a - a thing that was - obvious to him you could do, but you weren't doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about punctuality and tidiness and manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, you were - you were supposed to be there - they rang a bell in the morning 
and you were supposed to be in, if you came in after the bell - stopped ringing - you were taken aside and - given a few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What language did they like you to speak at the School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 The - the only language was - that we were taught in was English. We never had a lesson in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4010374\charrsid16062691 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 aelic. And I'm a native }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4010374\charrsid16062691 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
aelic speaker. My father and mother was - it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4010374\charrsid16062691 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 aelic we all spoke in the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When you went to school had you ever spoken in English before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No, well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 It must have been terribly difficult for the children wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Well the funny thing with them is this that - they go from that stage and among people of - who are - brought up - in English, hold their own. In fact - I maintained that - having a second language gives you a - a p
erception into things that you - you wouldn't understand otherwise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Wasn't it very difficult for the children when they were so young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, but then again - the teachers were trained that way, and they were very good, they were very patient with
 us. I still remember the - first teacher I had on the first primer and - I had the fondest regard for that girl all my life, she was very - very patient with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was she a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4010374\charrsid16062691 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
aelic speaker herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 So they could understand your language?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What about the headmaster, could he?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, he couldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did your parents take an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, not - well they took an interest, but they couldn't help us because - they didn't have that type of education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 But they encouraged you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes, oh very much so. Very much so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did they ever meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Ah, yes, quite often. Quite often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 On formal occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh - no, just - meeting them casually. Just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 There weren't meetings up at the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I don't remember my parents ever being in the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were there any gangs or groups of children in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 There wasn't one end of the village and the other end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Ah well, occasionally we'd go out and have skirmish, and throw stones at - each other, at - from a distance. Playing at - playing at being a - at - at war with one another, next day you were quite pally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Out of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Left out, who didn't get played with, who didn't join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
The only - people - the only - children that I know that were left out were - were - were those who opted out, themselves. Some - people - some - children - aren't built that way, they - they just - don't went to play.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What the Americans call loners,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, a loner, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were there any illegitimate children who were sort of outcasts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well - perhaps there'd be one or two but we weren't fussy, we just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 They weren't left out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. Oh no, not a bit of it. They were - they were soon accepted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 That was in 1917?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 17.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 F
irst year I went to work on a farm. Just for - the summer months. Tying - tying sheaves after the reaper. It wasn't a binder or - it was - or a harvester, it was just - a reaper, they cut it and - left the - enough to make a sheaf and we tied the bands on
 it and - stoked it up. Next year, next spring I - went to work in the Castle gardens here. And from then on I - Lord Leverhulme's schemes were - coming on apace. I started work on - on one of they schemes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Doing what sort of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh - first I w
as just - what - what they called a nipper. Going around - -with - drills - rock drills for - to the blacksmith's shop, for sharpening. Then I - gravitated into the blacksmith's shop myself and I took - three years in there. And that was - when I left - w
ell I was a year at home, a little over a year at home, from there to London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When you were at home were you going out fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Then you went to London, what work did you do there, did you get the boat there in London?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was that the Merchant Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Yes, Merchant Navy. Mm hm. First trip down to South America. Up the River Plate. From there - next one I think across to New York. Back again from there to New Zealand. Back again. One of the Blue Federal boats, round the 
land, France, Germany and Holland. And the second time I went across to New York - I was the rebel again, I took ship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What rank had you been, what job had you been doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Just - a deckhand, a seaman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What did you do then after you jumped ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I went to work as a blacksmith. About two years in there, I - went up to Detroit and I was working in the car factories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was that on the assembly line?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How long did you stick that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 About six and a half years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was that such well paid work then as it is now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
It was very well paid work. But - the unfortunate thing with us was that - it wasn't steady. The moment - there was a change of model every year, and the moment the model was changed the staff was reduced a
nd - the production was cut down, and so on. So that's what you - what you gained on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4010374\charrsid16062691 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691  merry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4010374\charrsid16062691  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 grounds you lost on the roundabouts. But it was very well - very good pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 What did you do after you left the motor works, what sort of job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Down to
 New York again. I started house building. I started working in New York, New York Foundling Hospital, and - I finished off with - twenty-two painters, two brass fitters, two joiners - doing the maintenance work for the New York Foundling Hospital.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You mean you were over them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. For nearly two years. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You were sort of foreman there were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. I took up sign}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4010374\charrsid16062691  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 writing. And that's what I do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 And you've done that ever since have you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Has that been your main source of income? Since you got back to Lewis?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
No. No, my main source of income was - wool waste most of the time. And - buying it from the weaver and sending it down to Yorkshire, but that - fell through, and - I always did some o
f the sign writing. But this year - I don't know what's happened - everybody seems to get - sign conscious. They want sign boards, they want lines written up and - names on their houses and - what have you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 So you've got a lot of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Quite a bit. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 It's good to hear somebody has because everybody seems very depressed about the island?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Very. Very. Very. I don't know how long this will last with me though, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I wanted to ask you a few questions about the jobs you had before 
the end of 1918, that would be the summer job in which you were binding up the sheaves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 That's - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 And the one in the gardens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well - 19 - 19 was the one in the gardens. 19 - 17 - I left school, and 19 - I worked to the farm that d
ay, that year, and - that - year after - the year after that I was - fishing most of the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Before you went to the gardens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes, before I went to the gardens. There was fishing in our house all the time, all the time, boats all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When you were fishing were you given any money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Oh well - the family was. We were - we got the fish, we were handed the fish and we turned it over, my mother and various other ladies left with a - a gig, our - our horse and - our gig, and sold it, u
p here. And they handled the money. Then of course there was another - one, they had a curer, what we called having it curer for the fish. The curer bought all the fish and sent - the money down maybe at the end of the week. Then there was a share out. Ah
,
 we did all right, we didn't do bad at all, and I - I was never - I was - I never starved - so much, as I starved in the States, the richest country in the world. And when you go five days without breaking bread - sleeping in the parks - you're just about
 - hit rock - rock bottom.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When you were doing the farm work, your first job, can you tell me what days of the week you worked and what hours? Did you work every day?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh you worked ever - every day of the week except Sunday. And the hourse were from six to six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No holidays and no pay hardly. The pay wasn't very big in those days. Eleven and three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4010374\charrsid16062691  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 pence a week. Eleven and three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4010374\charrsid16062691  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 pence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 At the time did you feel that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh yes, I was only glad to have it because - there wasn't very many boys - that could get a job like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was it a farm nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you give any of that money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 All of it. Practically all of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did she give you any back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Well if I wanted some back, and maybe I kept - a sixpence out or something like that. But - I felt like lord in the field, oh my - helping the family exchequer to that extent was something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How did you get on with the other people on the farm, were there several other people working there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. Yes. Fine. We were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You'd known them all your life I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How did your employer treat you, the farmer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Quite good. Quite good - of course we didn't eat there, we went home for our meals. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 It was near enough for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. But - he was - he was very nice, quite a nice man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 How did you feel about that work, did you like the work or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well I don't - I can't say that I did because I spent more time - picking - thistles out of my hands - at night than - it was sore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Was that the first money you'd earned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Excepting that - I was going around with the Solway Gazette when it first started and I was getting 
- maybe sixpence a week for selling two dozen papers. Aye. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you walk into Stornoway to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, no. No. They sent - the papers down to the school house and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You'd sell them to the people round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When did you start doing that, do you remember how old you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I really - don't - know, I - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Were you a teenager?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Oh no, well if I was in very very early teens. Must have been thirteen or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You were doing it for some years were you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
No, I don't think - you were given the option - after you left school. I'm not sure now, I'm not sure of that in my mind but - it fell to my - younger brother, youngest - not the youngest but - younger than me, and from him to my other brother I remember 
that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 It was sort of inherited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you serve an apprenticeship or training period for any of your jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Blacksmith - blacksmithing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You actually served your time there did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did you ever belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
No. Not - not - not in the blacksmith line, I did to - to the - to the weavers union here, after I came back. No we were no, no, there was no union, no car workers union if you spoke of the union - over with this you'd be - out on your ear b
efore - payday. They didn't want a union there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Did you feel that there were divisions of interest among workers, did you feel that people who had served their time, craftsmen and other workers had - were in conflict in any way, was there any difference between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I didn't feel that there was - each to his own job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When you started full time work would you say it changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Well, yes, I felt - more of a - complete individual, that I could stand on my o
wn two feet earning my own living. And at the same time contributing to the wellhood of the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Did you still carry on with your activities in the same way when you first started earning, having the same friends, doing the same sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. Because - I was living up here, in town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 When you were on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, no. No. Oh when I was on the farm? Ah I was only - it's only a matter of the summer months only.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 And then you were at home fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 There weren't any changes in your social life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No. No, but when I started the blacksmithing - I was away from home and I had to - there had to be a change.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You mean when you were working for Lord Leverhulme?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Yes. At least for Sir Robert McArthur, who was his contractor then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 
Would you say that starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all, or your brothers and sisters? Did it make any difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 No, that's the only difference that I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 You felt more of a man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I felt more like a - complete person than - that I could - keep myself and help - help them at the same time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Could you tell me the jobs that your brothers did? You had six brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Six brothers, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4921470 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 Did they all have very varied care}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4010374\charrsid16062691 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 rs like you've had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8137916 AM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6584537\charrsid16062691 I don't know, wait - wait a minute now. The first one, first -
\par }}